1. 0 permanent jobs created 2. 0 new businesses created • Cooperation with ODIMM is set up to provide the start-up and follow-up seminars-on-demand for beneficiaries who will initiate businesses on the left bank • 4 Cross-river Business Support Platforms (the both banks associations of Beekeepers, Fruit Growers and Essential Oil producers as well as Trade Chambers of Moldova and Transnistria) received 25 000 EUR grant support each for joint development programmes over next 2 years. Over 1800 farmers and SMEs are to benefit from training, mentoring, matchmaking and study visits support; • 45 left Bank tourist industry representatives, out of which 45 women, (from hotels, restaurants tourist agencies, guides and museum workers) improved their capacities through 2 one-week trainings conducted by joint team of experts from right and left bank;
3. 0 new local communities benefiting from small infrastructure projects (10 infrastructure projects - under various stages of development • 14 communities are beneficiaries of 14 infrastructure projects, which are at various stages of implementation (1- Rezina bridge lighting is completed). The projects include renovation of 4 sport grounds, 2 culture houses, 2 kindergartens and 2 schools; 1 community center, 1 park, 1 street illumination and 1 waste management. • Total number of people who will benefit from improved social infrastructure objects exceeds 70 000 people.
4. 10 NGOs and LPAs with improved capacity to implement development projects • 20 NGOs and LPAs are improving their capacities through 10 EU funded Community support small grants. Most of the of activities of these grant agreements are to be implemented in 2020, however some cultural events have already taken place. • 609 (395 women) representatives of LPAs and NGOs from both banks of Nistru river improved their project writing capacities during 4 informational meetings and 9 seminars conducted; • Around 243 NGOs and Professionals are involved in development of their 5 Cross -River Thematic Sectoral platforms, supported by EU CBM 5 grants;
5. 0 new joint collaborative infrastructure projects implemented • 11 Social infrastructure projects (14 sites – 14 benefitting communities) are at various stages of implementation, • 10 Community development small grants are at various stages of implementation (to be competed in 202-2021).
6. 2 common cultural public events • 1 Play Musical Festival was conducted in Bender Fortress, 8 Youth Orchestra concerts conducted at Tirnauca, Carmanovo, Ribnita, Ofatinti, Dubasari (2), Rascov and Camenca.
7. 1000 individuals in the public for those common cultural events • Around 2000 individuals (approximately 50% men and 50% women) participated at Play Musical festival at Bender Fortress and 8 concerts conducted by Youth Orchestra in various Culture Houses of Left bank (predominantly renovated by EU funds in previous CBM phases).
8. 0 historical cultural heritage related projects realized under the EU cultural heritage funds; (2 flagship projects and 10 cultural infrastructure projects - under various stages of development) • Technical expertise of both Flagship projects are conducted. • A complex tendering processes preceded by a thorough preparatory work was launched, which will result in Master plan elaboration of Bender fortress. • Cultural Heritage fund Implementation Modality is developed to set up procedures for provision of support to smaller scale Cultural heritage objects including unmaterial ones; • Cooperation between professionals from right and left banks on 2 Flagship projects was established through common visits and review/discussions, that further led to the establishment of the EU CBM Cultural Heritage Monitoring group that will also be involved in the identification and further monitoring of the restoration of10 small scale cultural heritage objects.
9. 0 co-productions produced • 1 informational seminar for 64 (30 women) for Media and production houses professionals (18 – from the left bank) with networking opportunities was conducted with the goal to identify applicants for joint media projects/co-productions; • A study tour for up to 10 media and production houses representatives to learn from experience of multicultural/multi-ethnic/multilanguage TV station is under preparation;
10. 0 co- productions /common media projects broadcasted • An open-end call for proposals (up to 60 000 EUR per grant) was developed, approved by the board and launched on October 9th to identify applicants for joint media projects/co-productions. 11. 0 diffusions on prime time of some supported media contents including the Transnistrian region • Both banks media outlets and production houses need assessment study was performed through about 30 in-depth interviews (21- on right bank and 9 – on the left bank of Nistru River.) The study results were used to develop open-end call for proposals to identify applicants for joint media projects/co-productions to be broadcasted on prime time of some supported media contents including the Transnistrian region.

